      <article class="article-content">
        <div class="article-body">
          <h2>Our Mission</h2>
          <p>Lumina was founded on a simple belief: that thoughtful writing about design, technology, and human experience can help us build a better future. In an age of algorithmic feeds and fleeting attention, we're creating space for deeper engagement with ideas that matter.</p>
          
          <p>We explore the intersection of creativity and technology—not as a niche, but as the defining territory of our time. Every article we publish aims to be both intellectually rigorous and genuinely useful, offering perspectives that help our readers think better, create better, and live better.</p>

          <h2>What We Cover</h2>
          <p>Our content spans several key areas:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Design</strong> — From interface patterns to design systems, we cover the craft and strategy of creating great experiences.</li>
            <li><strong>Technology</strong> — Not gadget reviews, but thoughtful analysis of how technology shapes society and how we can shape it in return.</li>
            <li><strong>Productivity</strong> — Evidence-based approaches to doing meaningful work in a distracted world.</li>
            <li><strong>Culture</strong> — The human side of working in tech, from team dynamics to remote work.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Our Team</h2>
          <p>Lumina is run by a small team of writers, designers, and developers who are passionate about sharing knowledge. Our contributors come from leading technology companies, independent consultancies, and academic institutions around the world.</p>

          <p>We believe diverse perspectives create better understanding. We're always looking for new voices to contribute to the conversation.</p>

          <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
          <p>Have a story idea? Want to contribute? Just want to say hello? We'd love to hear from you. Reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@lumina.blog">hello@lumina.blog</a> or find us on social media.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

